        sourceRef: 'Ruth 4:17-22; 1 Samuel 16:1-13',
        label: 'The Jesse Lineage — From Bethlehem to the Throne',
        connection: 'Jesse is David\'s father — an otherwise unremarkable farmer from Bethlehem. To speak of "the stump of Jesse" rather than "the stump of David" is to reach back behind the monarchy to its humblest origin. When Samuel came to Jesse\'s house to anoint a king (1 Samuel 16), he almost missed David — the youngest, the one in the fields, the one nobody thought to invite. The shoot from Jesse\'s stump carries this DNA: God\'s choice emerges not from the place of power but from the place no one is watching.',
