        connection: 'Isaiah 11:15-16 explicitly models the future deliverance on the original exodus: parting waters, dry ground, a highway through what was impassable. The Song of the Sea (Exodus 15) is the direct template for Isaiah 12 — the same vocabulary (yeshuah, ozzi v\'zimrat), the same movement from terror to praise, the same communal eruption of song after rescue. What God did at the Red Sea, God will do again at the Euphrates.',
